                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/1137.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-04T19:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1912—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Serious mutiny in Wuchang February 27. General condition of anarchy occasions
                    reasonable fear that foreign intervention may become necessary. Japanese are
                    bringing one more battalion to Tientsin from Manchuria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
